                        <div class="post-faq-card">
                            <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-4">Is the result of a hair transplant really permanent?</h4>
                            <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">Yes. Donor follicles taken from the back and sides of the scalp are genetically resistant to dihydrotestosterone (DHT), the hormone responsible for pattern baldness. When transplanted, they retain this resistance and continue growing for life. However, native hair in other areas of the scalp may continue to thin over time, which is why a long-term scalp maintenance plan is always recommended.</p>
